# Routes Access Alignment

- Route middleware must match intended controller access model.
- Do not tighten/relax route guards without checking controller ownership checks.
- For report/accounting endpoints, keep `authenticateToken`, private access, and superuser guards consistent.
- If access policy changes, update both route and controller layers in one task.

## Required validation after route access edits

- Verify impacted endpoints still map to correct permission behavior:
  - allowed actor gets success;
  - forbidden actor gets 403/404 per current contract.
- Run relevant smoke script(s) for modified domain.
